column5: The motor is a 2004 150 HP Optimax, with smartcraft gauge software version "3", according to startup screen. This harness has been left over from the professional rigging job that was done on my Ranger. It is from a binnicle control system with remote key switch,  that was converted to a side mount control box with integral key switch.   Harness ends:    Thanks in advance.
The bottom pic tells me it is for a temp sensor or oil reservoir.
Thanks! That will help to explain a lot.
Alot of Techs don't like to use the push on connectors. They,like myself replace them with terminal and nut. Over time the push on fall off by loosening by vibration.
